The paper deals with object detection, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves a novel gradient harmonizing mechanism, which is related to optimization and loss functions (cs.LG). The authors also mention the use of deep learning techniques, which falls under artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper involves training a neural network, which is a common topic in neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the authors evaluate their method on the MS COCO dataset, which is a common benchmark for object detection and falls under multimedia (cs.MM).
